0:The second I'd poked my head into school on Thursday, Misumi-kun immediately invited me to go see Ayase in the hospital with him.\p;
100:Given that the idea hadn't even crossed my mind, it'd caught me off guard.\p;
200:But before I'd even been able to respond, Rimi said she wanted to come too for whatever reason, and I ended up being swept along with her as a result.\p;
300:Now, let me be clear—I had a heart and all.\p;
400:But, considering the menace known as “Shogun” was drawing closer and closer to me, I didn't think this was exactly the time to show it.\p;
500:I... didn't wanna die...\p;
600:Coming in through the front entrance, Misumi-kun looked around the lobby in confusion.\p;
700:〔Rimi〕“What's wrong?”\p;
800:〔Misumi〕“Well, I was just tryin' to figure out where Kishimoto's room was.”\p;
900:Had he seriously come this far without knowing that? This guy was beyond belief sometimes...\p;
1000:〔Takumi〕“This is... the outpatient ward...”\p;
1100:〔Takumi〕“The hospital ward... is next door...”\p;
1200:〔Misumi〕“Shit, that right?”\p;
1300:〔Rimi〕“Dai-chiiin, get a grip already!”\p;
1400:AH Tokyo General Hospital.\p;
1500:It was the hospital I'd gone to ever since I was a kid—I'd even come here just the other day. So I was pretty knowledgeable on where everything was.\p;
1600:Dr. Takashina's face flashed across my mind, and I involuntarily groaned to myself.\p;
1700:As we walked to the hospital ward, Misumi-kun turned to me.\p;
1800:〔Misumi〕“So, which of these rooms is hers?”\p;
1900:〔Takumi〕“H-How should... I know...?”\p;
2000:This was a general hospital, so there were obviously a ton of different wards and departments. If I had to guess...\p;
2100:〔Takumi〕“P-Probably... not the surgery ward...”\p;
2200:〔Takumi〕“B-But... she could... maybe... be in the psychiatry ward...”\p;
2300:There hadn't been any visible injuries on Ayase after she'd fallen. And considering she'd attempted suicide, her mind had likely been brought to the brink, so her being in the psychiatric ward seemed very possible.\p;
